Conclusion
In this lab, you worked hands-on with Docker's persistent storage model, moving from basic volume creation and inspection through to backing up and restoring data, and finally deploying production-style MySQL and PostgreSQL containers on named volumes. You confirmed experimentally that data written to a volume survives container removal, restarts, and full recreation, which is the core guarantee that makes volumes suitable for stateful workloads like databases. You also built reusable backup and monitoring scripts, learning along the way that tools like psql require explicit credential handling, such as exporting PGPASSWORD, to run safely inside non-interactive automation. Overall, you now have practical experience applying Docker volume management, backup and restore workflows, and basic database persistence verification to real deployment scenarios.
